Conflicts: containerd
Replaces: containerd
Built-Using: ${misc:Built-Using}
Description: daemon to control runC
 Containerd is a daemon to control runC, built for performance and density.
 Containerd leverages runC's advanced features such as seccomp and user
 namespace support as well as checkpoint and restore for cloning and live
 migration of containers.
 .
 This package contains the binaries.
 .
 This package is frequently updated to new Containerd upstream versions, which
 may include new features and often introduce breaking changes. If you want
 stability, use containerd-stable instead.
